{
  "name": ".EOD: Sync + Summary + Decisions",
  "version": "7.1.0",
  "description": "Unified EOD routine: autonomous backend (Hedy ingestion, Asana sync, daily reset, organ cascade, compression, enrichment, experiments, git sync) then interactive frontend (day summary, decisions, Slack DM).",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the unified EOD routine.\n\nIMPORTANT: Richard is in Pacific Time (America/Los_Angeles). The system clock shows UTC. Subtract 7 hours (PDT) or 8 hours (PST) from any UTC timestamp to get Richard's local time. Today's date in Pacific is what matters for daily reset, carry-forward, and all date-based logic. Run `TZ=America/Los_Angeles date` to get the correct local time.\n\n---\n\n## PART 1: BACKEND (autonomous \u2014 no interaction with Richard)\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/eod-backend.md.\n\n### Backend Phases (execute in order)\n\n**Dependency chain:** Phase 1\u21922 is strict (meeting-derived tasks must exist before Asana reconciliation can run). Phases 3-5 are sequential but independent of each other. Phase 6 requires subagent context. Phase 7 aggregates all prior output.\n\n#### Phase 1: Meeting Ingestion\nIngest from Hedy + Outlook. Run meeting-to-task extraction and analytics. Must complete before Phase 2 because Asana reconciliation depends on meeting-derived tasks.\n\n#### Phase 2: Asana Reconciliation\nDelta sync, daily reset (Pacific date boundary), recurring task creation, completion moves, blocker detection.\n\n#### Phase 3: Organ Cascade + Maintenance\nCompression, workflow health checks, comms analytics, enrichment queue processing.\n\n#### Phase 4: Recurring Task State Checks\nGoal updater, calibration, scorecard. (wiki_lint removed 2026-04-18 \u2192 now runs via wiki-maintenance hook.)\n\n#### Phase 5: Housekeeping\nDuckDB snapshots, git sync, changelog updates, steering integrity checks.\n\n#### Phase 5.5: Wiki Candidate Contribution\nAfter Phase 5, if you observed a new pattern/decision/learning or a contradiction to an existing wiki article, append ONE line to ~/shared/context/intake/wiki-candidates.md:\n\n`[YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM eod] signal: <one sentence> | source: <path or ID> | proposed: <slug or \"enrich: existing-slug\">`\n\nNo analysis, no drafting, no deduplication. Max 3 lines per run. Skip silently if nothing observed.\n\n#### Phase 6: Experiments\nKarpathy CLI \u2014 subagents for blind eval.\n\n#### Phase 7: Compile Output\nProduce structured JSON for EOD-Frontend consumption.\n\n#### Phase 7.5: SharePoint Durability Sync\nPush artifacts to OneDrive \u2014 non-blocking.\n\n### Auto-Execute (proceed without asking Richard)\n- Daily reset — demote Today→Urgent at date boundary\n- Completion moves — shift done tasks to completed section\n- Organ cascade — propagate updates across body files\n- Market context — refresh metrics from DuckDB/SharePoint\n- DuckDB writes — snapshots, experiment logs, health rows\n- Git sync — commit and push shared/ changes\n\n### Queue for Frontend (approval required)\n\n#### Task Proposals\n- Recurring task creation proposals\n\n#### Carry-Forward Decisions\n- Carry-forward decisions beyond simple demotion\n- Example: Task blocked 7+ days with no owner change → propose escalation or backlog move, not just re-queue\n\n#### Blocker Confirmations\n- Blocker registry confirmations\n\nConstraint: This hook runs as direct agent turn (not subagent) because Phase 6 Karpathy experiments use subagents.\n\nAfter each phase, output: Phase N complete or Phase N failed: [reason]. Continue on failure.\n\n---\n\n## PART 2: FRONTEND (interactive \u2014 present to Richard)\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/eod-frontend.md.\n\n### Frontend Steps (present in order)\n\n| Step | Name | Content |\n|------|------|--------|\n| 1 | EOD summary | Completed, carried forward, new tasks, Five Levels, blockers |\n| 2 | Decisions needed | Recurring task approval, carry-forward decisions, blocker confirmations |\n| 3 | Portfolio + ABPS AI summary | \u2014 |\n| 4 | System health | Workflow health, compression, communication analytics, enrichment |\n| 5 | Experiment results | If Karpathy ran |\n| 6 | Slack DM summary | \u2014 |\n\nPresent decisions for approval. Execute approved writes. Follow Guardrail Protocol.\n\n=== COMMON FAILURES (read before executing) ===\n1. Timezone drift: daily reset MUST use Pacific date boundary (`TZ=America/Los_Angeles date`). Using UTC demotes wrong tasks \\u2014 a 10pm PDT reset on the wrong UTC date cascades errors into Asana. Always convert before any date-based logic.\\n2. Skipping Phase 6: Karpathy experiments require subagent invocation with independent context. Always run even near context limit \\u2014 experiments are the compounding mechanism that improves the system over time.\\n3. Over-prompting Richard: auto-execute actions (daily reset, completion moves, organ cascade, DuckDB writes, git sync) proceed without approval. Only queue items (task proposals, carry-forward decisions, blocker confirmations) need Richard."
  }
}